name: The Varsity
address: 61 North Avenue NW, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text: Not sure how anyone would eat at the varsity and expect anything but the varsity.    In this instance you can’t rate a place on what it isn’t.   It isn’t the best burger you’ve ever eaten but it will be the best varsity burger you’ve ever eaten.   I say that because 30+ years after I ate my first varsity they still deliver.    Of course the fries are a little limp, they aren’t processed crap…they are fresh potatoes.    The onion rings are battered there on the spot.       If you go to North Ave you might still see them in there peaking and cutting. Combo numbers shouldn’t be on the menu at the V but times have changed and  I see them.    I hate that the old school “crowd to the front ordering” doesn’t exist anymore.   You used to have to fight your way to the front and try to make eye contact with someone behind the counter if you ever hoped to eat.   In some cases you’d get to the front and realize you were in the fry and ring only line.     Eat here if you’re visiting but know what it is.    It is The V! I’m partial to a couple of dogs (they should come with chili unless you ask for them naked), cheese stake (because I liked the way they smash them to melt the cheese) and rings.   Always ask for a side (which should mean some chopped onions in a little piece of wax paper) and don’t skip the frosted O or PC on ice and a pie.

Coming to the Varsity feels a bit like stepping back into time. The menus are simple and you know what you’re getting into: fresh cut fries, burgers, and hot dogs. We recommend the chili dog and can’t go wrong with a cheeseburger. It’s nothing that you haven’t had before but is a good place with free parking to dine downtown or with kids. Note, if you’re looking for a place with lots of toppings this isn’t it: they keep things simple and classic here.

I had heard about this place before and decided to stop in here for lunch one day. I went to the counter where I ordered and received my food and then went and sat down at my table. I ordered a number one combo which consists of two chili dogs and fries. I also got a Coke zero float. The fries and hotdog were good. I thought the float had way too much ice cream compared to soda. Overall, the food was good and it was a cool atmosphere. I would definitely recommend trying this place.

If you are a baseball fan then this should be a stop. Just know the food hasn’t changed in 20 years. I had the slaw dog and it was a good choice on a hot dog. My husband’s chili dog however? Not good at all.

My very first time visiting this location. Years ago I went to the Norcross location called the Jr Varsity. I was near here years ago when I visited Apache Cafe. I had to visit to see the food menu for myself and see how it's hitting. I got a #1 2 chilli dogs with onion rings and a orange soda. I also got a #2 chilli cheese dog and burger with onion rings. The food is delicious! This is their staple the way that they prep and prepare the food they got to be doing something right for this long!I also got a peach pie and a apple pie delicious! Look at how long they have been in business and still going strong. I visited on 8-22-2025.

name: The Vortex Bar & Grill
address: 878 Peachtree St NE, Atlanta, GA 30309, USA

reviews.text: This is a very unique place that gives a great vibe of neighborhood, after work, or weekend meet-up vibe. The inside has animals, great wall art, and music is great. Our waitress was very helpful and prompt with our order. Burgers were definitely on point, just what I wanted. Cooked to my liking with a great selection of burgers. It is in midtown, so parking is where you can find it.

Food here is definitely a 4.5 stars. Love the atmosphere and service. The place is huge with many different areas  and an amazing decor.  If You like to drink, the bar is where is at. I would def recommend this place to friends and family and anybody staying in this area.

Absolutely the BEST bar in the city. Even with no crowd, the bar makes you feel welcomed. Noah and Emily were amazing! They made sitting down at the bar one of the most friendly experiences I’ve had in my time in the city. They also knew how to keep the positive energy up and kept me feeling lively with drink after drink (responsibly of course 😊😉)

Loved the funky vibe, friendly service, and amazing food! The burgers definitely lived up to the hype, just as the waitress promised. I really enjoyed the flavors and would happily come back for more.

Unique interior and vibes, with lots of vintage decorations. You can’t go wrong with the $3 mystery shots (served in medicine cups) — all the times I’ve gotten them, they’ve been strong and more than worth the price and mystery. The food is average and nothing too special. The service is great — everyone was very friendly and checked in on us often.

name: Ecco
address: 40 7th St NE, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text: My boyfriend and I came here for our 7 year anniversary. We received a note, and two glasses of wine on the house. The service was amazing, and the food was even more so!! Shoutout to our waiter, Mike. We will definitely be coming back ☺️

Finally tried Ecco with some friends ahead of a show nearby. Had a great experience overall and the food was solid but the service was the biggest standout.

Started with the burrata, bread service, stuffed peppers, and fried goat cheese balls. The latter was delicious, as was the bread, but the peppers let me down a bit.

Had the special as my main, lamb ravioli, and it was decent but not as good as my wife’s pappardelle.

Will have to try Ecco again before comparing with my favorite pasta spots but would give it a solid 7/10 from this initial visit.

Fun vibes and great cocktails.
We enjoyed the goat cheese balls and gnocchi. The cold asparagus was so interesting and delicious as well.
Came with a small group for dinner and had a great time. Our waiter was awesome and the food, drinks and ambiance were all just right. Would be happy to come back again.

Sat at a lovely table outside. The food was great. Parker made our experience very easy and wonderful. Great server. Very knowledgeable of the menu and awesome personality. The goat cheese and black spaghetti are 10/10. Will be back!

name: Fresh To Order - Midtown
address: 860 Peachtree St NE, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text: A great associate named Isaac assisted me during my last visit. He gave EXCELLENT service while assisting me with my order. I Love the menu variety this restaurant offers. As a vegetarian I know I can always find suitable options. The Black Bean Burger is one of the best I've had. I also love the Mediterranean Quinoa Salad. It's in a great location in the heart of Midtown. They have great patio space to dine outside. It's one of my favorite places to grab something tasty when on the go. Lately I've been ordering the salmon. It's done well and seasoned to satisfaction. Highly recommended!

The food is always good and healthy. You can’t miss with the Asian chicken crunch and Asian salad but everything I’ve had was good. The customer service is the best in Atlanta. On two different occasions Isaac and T went above and beyond. Isaac didn’t rush my family out during closing and kept assuring us it was ok and making sure we had everything. T kept checking on us, giving us to go boxes, making sure the order was right and that we enjoyed everything. Second to none, please reward them, I’m now a customer for life.

I really enjoy Food 2 Order. The food is healthy, very reasonably priced, delicious and the menu has an excellent selection. The tortilla soup is particularly savory and not spicy. With my entre I usually order the wild rice and will spoon a little from the soup onto the rice.  On nice weather days the patio seating is perfect for getting out of the AC and viewing the pedestrians on Peachtree St. Their service is prompt and very friendly. It’s excellent food that is not fast food and a good choice for a nice meal.

The food is delicious here! All of the staff were friendly and it is a comfortable and clean restaurant. Everything we ordered was fresh and tasty. The soups are wonderful and the sandwiches are savory and made perfectly. We will definitely eat here again!

Very delicious and affordable salads. The Mediterranean salad was great. Lots of flavors and textures. The croissant was good tooo.  The chicken tortilla soup was too salty but had lots of chicken. Fast and friendly service.

name: Hudson Grille Midtown
address: 942 Peachtree St NE, Atlanta, GA 30309, USA

reviews.text: Cool experience. Had a good work and wanted to work my food off and I feel like it was a good experience. They were doing some work behind the bar so I didn’t expect to be greeted right away which wasn’t a problem at all. Perry was great, very sweet, professional and a good bartender. The salad was amazing though. Fresh ingredients and the house made ranch is always a plus.

Okay so on Sept 4 I ordered 2 of the chicken teriyaki bowls through Ubereats but did the pick up option when I tell you my food was so good! It made me want to come again to get it so today September 8 ordered the 2 chicken teriyaki bowls again through Ubereats pick up option  my rice was so mushy it’s not good at all not the same quality that I received the first time I am not sure what happened but it’s greatly disappointing I was bragging on this dish. Below are pics posted from the 1st visit

The loaded nachos and sides were definitely worth trying. However, I found the burgers a bit underwhelming as they lacked the flavor and juiciness I usually look for. If you're finding a good, satisfying burger in town, I’d personally recommend checking out The Vortex besides them instead. (Just a personal opinion, not a promo!)

Taco Tuesday was great!  The server Jordan was very attentive. Our team was very satisfied with the food and service. I also wants to give a big shout out to Aiesha. She has been a server of ours on several occasions and is always the best. Great staff at this location.
Very friendly staff and lots of TV. They didn’t play the sound of the game though. Wings were small but good sauce.

name: Cypress Street Pint & Plate
address: 817 W Peachtree St NW, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text: Fun and relaxing place, with good range of beers on tap and every day $3 pint specials.   Service is friendly and quick despite a very busy Friday night.  Large seating capacity inside and out.  Burgers are great.  Light My Fire cocktail was nice. Giant pretzel was soft, salty, and yummy, a bit skimpy in provided cheese and mustard but nice anyways.  We really loved our evening here and met a lot of nice people.  I’m in my sixties and was more than twice as old as the crowd which made it all the more enjoyable.

I just had lunch here today! I was pulled in by the big patio. The service was very mediocre. I had. Fish and chips. Fish was good. Slaw …not so much.We also ordered a med cheeseburger. It came out Mid well. I guess we just couldn’t want it Medium. I did notice that the other server or assistant that was working the patio area touched every table except ours. It was definitely giving…35, 35 miles..let’s just say I don’t think we fit the culture. Wouldn’t return.

Great place for drinks and casual food. Super affordable beers and IPAs. Good atmosphere as well — I usually like to sit outside if the weather is nice. Can get somewhat crowded during busy times, especially if you want to find a seat outside. Inside vibe is like a dive bar. Can get a bit loud both inside and outside. Service is friendly but can be a bit slower if it’s busy. Strawberry lemonade drink is super good

We were staying in Midtown and wanted somewhere close enough to walk. This was less than a 10 minute walk from the Fox. Great menu. Really great service from Gregory! They had us in and out in way under an hour on a Saturday night. The nachos and chicken and rice bowl were awesome! We’ll be back for sure.

We walked over to this restaurant from our hotel because of the ratings. Boy are we glad that we did. The service was great. The drinks and food were delicious and we really enjoyed the buzz and atmosphere of the place. If you are in town I would definitely recommend giving this restaurant a try. You won't regret it. Highly recommend. Pro tip: when you arrive scope out a table and grab it as it is first come first served.

name: J. Christopher's
address: 950 W Peachtree St NW, Atlanta, GA 30309, USA

reviews.text: French toast, sausage links and potatoes will cost you about $22 here. in my opinion, you can tell the food isn’t made fresh to order. the potatoes were hard, sausage could’ve been cooked a little bit more (still had a good flavor), but the French toast was hitting!

I’ve dined in twice and picked up once so I think it’s time to review. The take out was an omelet that had very few insides, all on one half only. Was not happy. First done in Danny was my server and I loved him. Made some recommendations and left me with a whole carafe of coffee bc he saw I needed it. The pimento cheese and bacon omelet was perfect it and I crave it constantly!  Biscuit and grits good size too.  Third trip had the western omelet biscuit and grits.  Smaller grits and dried biscuit. Odd for a 715 service. I didn’t catch the waitress name bc she didn’t offer it.  Didn’t bring necessary items for my take home items but quickly got them when asked. In the one picture it shows mid week specials. Can’t beat $7 for omelet (super stuffed too!) and sides.

We at breakfast at J. Christopher’s on Tuesday, November 5th at 9:30AM.  The  food and service ( by server Margaret ) were very good.  I would recommend J. Christopher’s and will have breakfast there again.

I have celiac and I loved this place. They were happy to make the eggs Benedict with gluten-free toast and the side of fruit was very fresh. My husband had the blueberry crunch cake and really enjoyed it as well.

This place is jumping OFF!!! I wasn't sure at first because I saw that they did not have a lot of waiters and waitresses and it was only two Cooks but I have to tell you the manager stepped up cleaning off tables doing silverware and the cooks and the waiters and waitresses rocked out. I was probably like 7th on the list and waited like 10 minutes. It was worth the wait the food is delicious, the French toast is awesome and those grits are to die for so just make sure you get the Grits if you come visit. Definitely recommend this place for some good breakfast and you can go on your way and it's not that expensive

name: Starbucks
address: 867 Peachtree St NE, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text:
⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

The Starbucks at 7th & Peachtree in Midtown Atlanta sets the gold standard for customer experience. The team here is consistently outstanding—friendly, professional, and remarkably attentive. Every morning, I’m greeted by name, my order is remembered without hesitation, and I always leave feeling valued and uplifted.

This location goes far beyond simply serving coffee. The staff demonstrate genuine hospitality, creating a welcoming environment that builds loyalty and community. Their ability to connect on a personal level—while also maintaining speed, accuracy, and consistency—is rare and deeply appreciated.

In a fast-paced Midtown environment, this Starbucks has become an anchor point of reliability and positivity. It’s clear the team takes pride in their work and in the relationships they cultivate. I cannot overstate how impactful that is for customers like me who start their day here.

To corporate leadership: this store is a shining example of what the Starbucks brand represents at its very best.

— A Grateful Regular

When you can’t even get oatmeal right or even a “hello/good morning” from any employee, it’s time to stop giving this company any money. The quality of food, drinks, and customer service continues to plummet while the prices keep going up for subpar everything. What used to be a consistent 5 star experience is anything but that which is truly disappointing.

I went inside and asked for a cup of water and was told I could not get one without a purchase. I told them I can provide proof of a purchase at a different location up the street and I was told I have to make a purchase there. So I then asked if I use my points because I currently have 280 can I then have a water. The male at the register rudely told me no I can’t use my points and get a cup of water. I then asked another staff member for there store number and the young Asian girl asked why I needed it I explained to her I wanted to report the service. She then confirmed even if I use my points on a food purchase I still could not have a cup of water! Wow!!! Okay Starbucks I have been consistently buying with you guys for years this service at this store is disgusting. I think I need a long break from you guys.

I get a matcha with an extra scoop of matcha and somehow despite the number of scoops being on the side of the cup the baristas will put less than the standard amount of matcha every time, and they forget the classic syrup if you ask them to remake it. The end product is a cup of green oat milk.
Good staff,and ice coffee100% recommended

name: Marlow's Tavern
address: 950 W Peachtree St NW #215, Atlanta, GA 30309, USA

reviews.author_name: Down The Road with Brian Mallard
reviews.text:
It was our first visit to this establishment and we were very pleased. The food was delicious and the service was perfect. The only possible drawback is the lighting is very low which might be an issue for some but for me it wasnt an issue.
Delicious food and great service, definitely recommend!

Wandered in at random but was pleasantly surprised!  The tavern vibe was great but the food was significantly elevated. We had the crab dip for an appetizer- bravo on the buttered saltine crackers!  Entrees were the Brisket Grilled Cheese (with onion rings) and the Shrimp and Crab Louie - each delicious. The only demerit was given because the center of the crab dip was cold. This places deserves a revisit to try more dishes.

Marlow’s Tavern in Midtown is a consistently satisfying neighborhood spot that does exactly what a modern tavern should—serves elevated comfort food in a welcoming, stylish setting. The ambiance strikes a perfect balance between upscale and relaxed, with cozy booths, communal tables, and a patio that’s great for sunny afternoons.

The food definitely delivers. Favorites like shrimp and grits—built on deep-fried white cheddar grit cakes—and Parmesan truffle fries stand out as inventive yet approachable tavern classics.
Service, even when busy, was quick and efficient—everything came on time, and the food tasted crisp and fresh.   I’ve found the bar area particularly fun too; the bartenders are “great,” and it feels just right for a casual lunch, game day, or a relaxed evening out.

Every visit feels reliably good—welcoming, flavorful, and lively without trying too hard. If you’re looking for solid tavern food with a neighborhood atmosphere in Midtown, Marlow’s Tavern is a smart go-to.

Would you like a shorter version or help highlighting a specific menu item?
My home! My wife loves this location! Food is always good! Service is always on point! Perfect for a quick bite!

An amazing last meal in Atlanta thanks to Josh and the staff.  Was in town for three days had great food but the service here really capped off our trip since they found out it was our first time complementary homemade cheese nachos. Josh thoroughly went over the menu and based on his recommendations we have the brisket sandwich, the French dip, Caesar salad, and the asparagus fries.  All of the food was great. We will definitely be back and when we go again, ask for Josh.

name: Publik Draft House
address: 654 Peachtree St NE, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text: Our lovely hotel concierge discreetly recommended PDH over the hotel restaurant for lunch and I’m so grateful she did. We had mussels to start and they were full of flavor and delicious, I wanted to drink the leftover sauce but our waiter brought us crispy bread and saved me the embarrassment. We also shared fried catfish and french dip, both were fantastic. Very lively but relaxed atmosphere, on top of it all our waiter Jordan was an absolute peach.

Publik is across the street from my hotel so I went there for a quick bite upon arrival. I had the special Fried Green Tomato sliders and the garlic string beans. Both very good. Lord of garlic on the string beans. The sliders were very tasty. It was a good experience.

Fantastic!! Burgers were juicy and packing with flavor! Loaded potato soup was by far the best I have had thus far but appears to not be a regular menu item. My daughter really enjoyed the fried catfish with the light cornmeal breading. Both my adult children raved about the coleslaw. Our server was friendly, attentive and knowledgeable. Great location as we stayed across the street at The Georgian Terrace. Cool vibe. Definitely would recommend and revisit.

We tried PDH before a show at the Fox since it is right beside the venue. We tried several appetizers and a salad. Everything was very tasty and a great combination of flavors. My only tips would be to add hooks under the tables for ladies to hang their purses. Also, the tables are a little small but not much you can do about that. Service was good, not great. We ordered one mixed drink and it was very weak. Overall, we will definitely come back to try more options the next time we go to the Fox.

We came before a show and had a fabulous experience here. Brandon was out server and he is really really really good at his job. He was observant, attentive, friendly, and had excellent knowledge of the food and drinks available. We never ran out of anything, the entrees came out soon after we finished the appetizer, refills came before we ran out and the food was delicious. The burrata was fresh and the bread was crunchy and soft, just how I like it. We both got the mushroom ravioli and honestly it was divine.  The mushroom, garlic, basil, cheese flavors mixed so well, I looked forward to every bite!  We were too full for dessert but I'm sure it would have been wonderful as well. Thank you PDH for a perfect dining experience in a time where dining experiences seem to be declining. I will definitely be back, and I would recommend PDH to anyone downtown for an event.❤️

name: Gyro Bros.
address: 85 5th St NW B, Atlanta, GA 30332, USA

reviews.text:
The service was polite and quick. We ordered a gyro, gyro plate, chicken strips and gyro burger. All entrees were delicious!

The gyro meat was cooked to perfection with and seasoned mildly with a balance of spices.  Its profile hinted at a predominant beef composition. The accompanying tzatziki sauce, while light in texture, offered a burst of fresh, vibrant flavor. This dish combination of seasoned meat and tangy sauce always makes for a wonderful dining experience.  It's a dish worth returning for for sure.

The accompanying Greek salad, with a balsamic sauce, was fresh and crisp. The chicken strips were tender breast meat with perfectly light and crispy breading. The burger and fries were generous portions.

3.5 stars. This is one of the better restaurants in the midtown district right next to Georgia Tech. My cousin comes here often so he got us here for a late lunch. The service is quick. Seating present outside and inside. I particularly enjoyed their spanakopita, dolmades and the falafel. The gyro plate was ok. They didn't have a working bathroom so we ended up using one in the restaurant next door. This is a solid option for food. Not much ambiance wise.

I ordered a Gyro combo (Gyro and salad). Cost about $15.

Food was 3/5 aka average. It was decent for the price. I’ve had gyros from all over the country and I kept help but feel that the Tzatziki sauce was lacking in flavor a tad bit. I was kind of sad about it as that’s my favorite part.

Loved the side salad with the Greek balsamic dressing. The veggies were fresh and crunchy. The dressing kind of saved the gyro for me when I added the dressing to it.

Good portions for the price. Which is why they got 4 stars instead of 3.

The atmosphere is good too, they had Rush Hour playing on the tv so it was a vibe. Good customer service, the employees there were nice and the place was clean. It is a small space however, but it was fine for me as I dined alone. Would be a nice place to grab lunch during a lunch break at work.
Tried the caesar salad, which was solid, for $7.80. Veggies were fresh and clean. The inside was smoky and greasy but there’s also seating outside.

This is the worst Mediterranean food I have ever had. The hummus isn’t good, the sauces are realllyyyyy bad, the falafel is fine & the spanakopita was okay fresh but I heated it up in my air fryer and it was disgusting. It was one of the most disappointing food experiences I have had in a long time. Convenience is not worth how truly inedible this place is.

name: Livingston Restaurant + Bar
address: 659 Peachtree St NE, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text:
We recently celebrated our daughter’s high school graduation at Livingston Restaurant—our go-to spot before Sunday matinees at the Fox Theatre. Located in the elegant Georgian Terrace Hotel at the corner of Peachtree and Ponce de Leon, Livingston delivered an unforgettable experience.

Brunch was absolutely delicious, with every dish—from the shrimp and grits to the chicken and waffles, avocado toast, French toast, and more—prepared to perfection. The flavors were rich, satisfying, and memorable.

A special shoutout to LaMonte, our bartender, for the amazing drinks, and to our exceptional waiter Hassan, who even doubled as our photographer, helping us capture candid moments of the day.

Thank you to the entire staff for going above and beyond to make our celebration truly special. We couldn’t have asked for a better place to mark such an important milestone. Thank you, Livingston, for a wonderful and heartfelt exerience.

3.5 stars - We came here for Mother’s Day brunch and we had people flying in so we had to change our reservation from 2pm to 4pm which I did on open table. My mom lives in Atlanta and said they don’t serve food at 4 PM so how could you possibly change the reservation. I called the restaurant multiple times and could not get through. Finally, I called the hotel and the person who answered the phone couldn’t give me any information except that the restaurant was closed at 4 PM and I said why would OpenTable allow me to change the reservation to 4 PM if they’re closed… And so finally I got put through to the head of food and beverage and she was very nice and told me that because it was Mother’s Day they would be serving at 4 PM.   But I had to call several times because the restaurant wasn’t answering🙄
My mom loves the room so that’s why I booked….but because we were 5 people we had a booth and it was really low and the table high 🤷‍♀️The food was very good but the service was exceptional. Our server Tamil was amazing and perfect 💗💗💗 she made the experience 💗

We had a dinner reservation for 4 at 6 pm on Saturday, 8/3/24. We were seated right away. Apparently the complimentary bread service has to be requested. We were dressed up because we were going to a play at the Fox. It was nice inside.

I split an appetizer and 2 entrées with my friend. We also got a side for the table. Here’s what I had:
- Peach, Burrata, & Prosciutto ($16): It was decent. I’ve had better.
- Lemon Asparagus Risotto ($30): Very small portion for the price. It was okay.
- Seabass ($48): This was the star of the show. The seabass was absolutely delicious. I also enjoyed the coconut forbidden rice, shitakes, and sugar snap peas that it came with.
- Brussels Sprouts ($12): Super good!! Perfectly crispy and seasoned.

Others in my party got the She Crab Soup ($12)—which came in the tiniest cup and I was told it was way too salty, Wedge Salad ($12)—I was told it was fine, Ahi Tuna Poke ($16)—fine, but needed more sauce.

I got the Mary Pickford ($12) for my drink and it was too strong for my taste.

Highly recommend the seabass and Brussels sprouts! Everything else was just meh.
good service and good brunch in the bar area same price/menu  as the sit down restaurant with limited staff. Even if the restaurant is empty Make reservations if you want to have a sit down meal.

Food was just OK for me. Most people in our group liked it, but I'm more selective mainly because I cook. I didn't care for the Caesar Salad or Creme Brulee. The Caesar was more like a wedge salad and i don't like them. The Creme Brulee was watery and wasn't sweet enough for my liking. The Butternut Ravioli wasn't very favorable. However, service and ambiance were great!

name: Ray's New York Pizza
address: 26 5th St NW, Atlanta, GA 30332, USA

reviews.text: Ray’s New York Pizza in Midtown is a solid spot if you’re craving classic, no-frills pizza. 🍕 The slices are huge, cheesy, and loaded with flavor—just like you’d expect from a New York–style place. The crust has that perfect balance of crispy and chewy, and they’ve got plenty of topping options to mix things up. The atmosphere is laid-back and casual, making it great for a quick bite after classes or a night out. Service is fast, prices are fair, and you definitely won’t leave hungry. A true Midtown staple!

I had the veggie 14” pizza 🍕 here. The crust was very loose like watery texture which was not enjoyable to eat, the taste was okay. The garlic knots were delicious with marinara sauce.. overall take your chance and try other items on the menu here. I wouldn’t go for the pizza again since I like my crust to be crunchy and not watery/loose. Thanks.🌱

Max was extremely helpful and patient with us while we struggled with making a decision! We got the ceased salad and deluxe pizza, which were both very filling and we had to take left overs back to the dorms. It’s very conveniently placed for GT students. Thanks Max!!

We loved this place! The general manager was incredibly kind to us (and everyone else we saw him interact with), the service from our server Ty was beautifully executed, and our food was delicious! It was a busy Saturday night but we still felt cared for and appreciated. We will be back! Thank you guys for a wonderful evening! Much love and many blessings!
Edit:the steak and cheese calzone and the cheese pizza were yummy ❤️

OMG, when I walked in the doors the smells inside the restaurant, quickly took me back to my days as a Sous chef at Giovanni's Italian restaurant in Memphis, I was no older than 13, and I cut my culinary teeth there! The atmosphere is both, inside and outside. And it is perfectly suited to the Mailu of Italiano!!

name: The Steamhouse Lounge
address: 1051 W Peachtree St NW, Atlanta, GA 30309, USA

reviews.text: I love this place!  We always get the oysters Rockefeller to start us off and Rum Punch. Alexis is the best server ever. And Mitch, the manger, is Mr Incredible!  He recommended the chocolate dipped key-lime island freeze: heavenly💗

Good servers. Good food. Great corn on the cob. Nice tacos. Great salads. Fantastic bottomless ice lemon tea, lemonade, half & half.

2024 August

Been to The Steamhouse Lounge many times and it never disappoints. Easy to walk to and very friendly service with excellent food. Sitting on the roof deck with food and drinks just can't be beat as you can see everything happens on the busy street. One warning though, the drinks are very good and very strong and always taste amazing. Not sure how they do that.

I paid a visit on a Saturday night. You can chose any where to sit downstairs, upstairs or outside on the 1st floor patio.
The food offering specialises in sea food and especially oysters.  NOTE, there is no draft beer available.
Large menu and plenty of bottled beer options.
Good, sea shack style decor.
I didn't eat, so can't comment on food service or quality.

Hesitant to post this because I want to keep it chill so I can get a spot at the Bar. If you have not tried it you should. Food is always great and the Bartenders do a great job making you feel welcomed even when you are just landing there after a long day away from home on a work trip. Quickly becoming a Atl Mid Town favorite for me.

name: Papa Johns Pizza
address: 990 State St NW, Atlanta, GA 30318, USA

reviews.text:
Date of Visit: 5/25/2025
Time: Approximately 10:00 PM – 10:37 PM
Manager on Duty: Michael Hobbs

I had an incredibly disappointing experience at this location. I arrived for a pickup order and waited over 30 minutes, which is unacceptable. When I first walked in, no one acknowledged me. name: Tabla

reviews.text:
A Culturally Curious Bite

My Honest Take on This Indian Restaurant

About a week ago, I visited this Indian restaurant and ordered their curry chicken with a side of spiced rice (I can’t recall the exact name of the rice, but you’ll recognize it in the photo). At first glance, everything looked good—but after tasting it, a few things stood out that made me curious enough to look deeper into how Indian cuisine is traditionally prepared.

I’ve been to several Indian restaurants around Atlanta, especially in the suburb Cities, because Indian food is honestly one of my favorite cuisines. At those other spots, I took the time to ask the chefs and staff questions about how they cook their curry chicken—whether it’s region-specific, or if it’s adapted in any way for other countries taste. Most of them shared that authentic Indian curry can vary depending on the region, but there’s usually a consistent depth of flavor, spices, and cooking technique that preserves the cultural roots of the dish.

What I’ve learned is that while some restaurants do blend their dishes with other countries influence for a different texture or flavor, others prefer to keep the cuisine strictly traditional. A few chefs even told me that keeping cultural dishes separate and true to their origin allows people to really experience the taste and story behind each country’s food.

That’s why this visit stood out. The curry chicken here tasted noticeably different from what I’ve experienced at other Indian spots. It had its own flavor profile, and the rice—while flavorful—was a bit too oily for my liking. Maybe that’s just how this type of rice is prepared, but compared to what I’ve tried before, it felt heavier than usual.

Now, this isn’t to say the food was bad—it just wasn’t what I expected based on my past experiences. Every restaurant has its own approach, and I respect that. For someone who’s new to Indian cuisine or enjoys fusion-style dishes, this place might be a great entry point. But if you’re like me and you’ve tasted more traditional versions of Indian cuisine, you may notice the difference right away.

At the end of the day, I appreciate any place that sparks curiosity and gets me thinking more about food and culture—and this spot definitely did that. It reminded me that every dish has a story, and sometimes, it’s worth digging a little deeper to taste the difference.

The best Indian food ever had so far in Atlanta! I went there twice within two days and the food is amazing. I especially like the Handi Gosht in chef signature. I LOVE spicy so I told the chef to make it 3 times spicier than normal and it was just right for me. So good!

Appetizer wise I usually get some samosas, the lasooni cauliflower is nice, the chicken tikka, or the chicken malai. Their garlic naan is also fresh and tasty.
