While the food was delightful, the service was unfortunately a bit slow.  Despite the wait, the delicious dishes and refreshing drinks almost made up for the pacing.  It's a recommended spot for anyone seeking quality Mexican cuisine, just be prepared for a leisurely dining experience. Oh and the valet parking situation could be better.

Food was delicious - cooked well and seasoned well. Margaritas were also well made. Vibe was fantastic. Music was a bit too loud to have a normal conversation even on the tables away from the bar but otherwise great experience. Would visit again.

This restaurant is awesome.  Outstanding value for great food, cute decor, and good service.

Had it not been for serving my Coke in a plastic bottle I'd have given five stars.  There's just no excuse for not having a soda gun when you have a full liquor bar.
Was staying at a nearby hotel and stumbled upon this place. Super cute environment. I enjoyed great service. The nachos and my margarita was delish. Made right!
Love this place. The service is amazing. The food and drinks are really good and a good price. Jorge was a great server definitely will be back

name: Seven
address: 860 Peachtree St NE, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

name: Tin Drum Asian Kitchen & Boba Tea Bar - Georgia Tech
address: 88 5th St NW, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text: A love letter in dining: I wont be able to fully describe how life changing this restaurant is, but I’ll do my best. Tin Drum has a special place in heaven and my heart. Over the past two months, I have spent close to $250 on Tin Drum. The food is the BEST Asian I have had in Atlanta in two years. Hands down. The ramen with pork belly, Singaporean curry noodles, and most of all, Chinese-Mongolian stir fry with pork belly and mushrooms are incredible. With the brown sugar milk tea, Thai tea, or pineapple peach tea, it physically hurts me when I go a week without eating their food. Don’t be afraid to try their fried chicken sandwich and crinkle fries — better than any burger and fries I’ve had in a long, long time. Been hooked since the first time. Can’t describe how good the food is, only my photo album filled with Tin Drum can. The service is so fast, employees so nice, restaurant so clean, and energy both peace and alive. With only $10-15 per bowl, it is one of the cheapest options for good quality food out here. As a food loving Tech student, I’ve been to all Tech Square restaurants, but none of them compares to Tin Drum. Tin Drum isn’t just a restaurant— it’s a way of life. It’s my safe haven. It’s my home.
The portions are huge!! Recommend the Thai curry and Singapore noodles. Parking is a bit hard to find but the food was great

I love Tin Drum in Tech Square—it's fast, flavorful, and super convenient. The self-order kiosks make lunchtime a breeze, and things move quickly even when it's busy. They serve everything from ramen and lo mein to panang curry and creative boba. A favorite: the chicken lettuce wraps and chicken lo mein are both reliably delicious  .

The menu offers a great variety of Pan-Asian dishes, all cooked fresh and customizable too—ideal when you're on-the-go or craving something different  . Many reviews highlight friendly service, consistent quality, and the quick pace—even referring to it as a “safe haven” and a “home” for students  .

A perfect choice for a satisfying, fast, and flavorful meal right in the heart of Tech Square.

Great restaurant if you have a bit of time. Ordering was pretty quick because you use tablets. I appreciate that the water refill is accessible to anyone instead of having to ask someone to refill it every time like other restaurants. Our food came out relatively quickly. I got lo mein with chicken. The chicken was very good and the sauce was as well. For the price point, it has very good food.

We had never eaten there. As you walk in there were some tablets and no cashier. The ladies behind the register saw us standing in line and didn’t bother to tend to us for 10 minutes. She then explained that they do not have cashiers and that you order on the tablet. That would have been helpful to know. The food and drinks were delicious I wish they had one in my town. The service was not good but I think once you know how to order and that the “waitresses” are motivated there to assist then you will be ok. We did not wait long for the food. The drinks with some sort of bubbles were exceptional!!

name: Tiff's Treats Cookie Delivery
address: Square on Fifth, 848 Spring St NW Ste B, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text:
Tiff’s Treats is my go-to whenever I’m craving something sweet or need a last-minute gift. The cookies always arrive warm, soft, and freshly baked, which makes the whole experience feel special. Delivery is usually quick and reliable, and the packaging keeps everything neat and presentable.

The chocolate chip and snickerdoodle are my personal favorites, but honestly, every flavor I’ve tried has been delicious. I also appreciate how easy it is to order through their app—super convenient.

The only downside is that prices are a bit on the higher side, but given the quality and the fact that they come straight to your door fresh out of the oven, it feels worth it. Overall, highly recommend Tiff’s Treats for a sweet pick-me-up or thoughtful surprise for friends and family!

I stopped by Tiff’s Treats to grab some cookies and was pleasantly surprised by how good they were. The chocolate pecan and double chocolate flavors? Absolute perfection — gooey, rich, and just what I needed for a late-night snack. Warm cookies that hit the spot every time. I’ll definitely be back when the sweet tooth strikes again!

Cookies were hot and fresh. Taste good not too sweet, just right in my opinion
Only issue I had was we didn’t eat them all right away and they got stale after 4 days

Got a great deal for Tiff’s on “Too Good to Go” and I appreciate them supporting that app! Don’t ding the packaging, it’s supposed to be minimal :) The staff was great and cookies were excellent. My family of 4 had them devoured in minutes.

They have better locations around the city. I tried them yesterday and cookies didn't taste that fresh/cooked right. I would give them 6/10 in comparison to their other locations around town which are like 9/10. Not coming back. Service was good.

name: Atwoods Pizza Cafe
address: 817 W Peachtree St NW Suite A105, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text: This pizzeria is a delightful surprise! Their Neopolitan pies are some of my favorite pizza in Atlanta. Show me your Roni is my indulgence, with pepperoni and sausage. Or the Pepe, with just pepperoni. They're served personal style and even if you think you can't eat the whole pie, it's so good that you probably will! We usually get a salad to balance out the meal, love their garden salad.They're made with high quality ingredients and a perfect crust. We come here at least 1 or 2 times a month, and the place is usually hopping with Georgia Tech students. You probably wouldn't even know this pizzeria is here, tucked in a ground floor corner of the old Biltmore Hotel. But it's definitely worth seeking out, highly recommend!!

This has only happened once in my life before with pizza.

I took one bite of their pizza and realized I made a terrible mistake.

1. The pizza I ordered would NEVER be enough to satisfy the greed of my taste buds fully, and I KNEW my diet was instantly ruined for the day.

2. I ordered a LARGER pizza to go (for later), and it never even made it to my fridge. I was tempted to take a little taste and ate the whole thing at the kitchen counter. Forgive me, Lord, I am weak. Lol

3. I ate pizza today like it was Thanksgiving, Christmas, and Easter all in one, and when I woke up from my binge-eating nap, the only thing that stopped me from getting another was their business hours.

The staff, manager, and cooks were excellent, professional, and friendly.
They took our order and served the pizzas fast, hot, and well-cut.

The basic cheese and pepperoni pizzas were excellent. So good that my picky eight-year-old spontaneously announced how good the pizza was later this evening and she rarely considers a meal after the fact.

The Buffalo Chicken pizza was better than any I have tasted. It was smooth, with mild blue cheese undertones, and just the right amount of buffalo sauce The chicken was sliced tender and the BREADING WAS STILL CRUNCHY!
It would have been some of the best chicken strips I ever had by themselves, let alone as a pizza topping. The toppings and sauces were balanced perfectly. The crust was thin but not soggy or dry and freshly made.

Make no mistake, this was a LOT of food. I am a shoelace under 280 and built like a (retired) defensive end. This pizza was so delicious I ate like when I was powerlifting.

Price-wise, it was a steal. I could have fed my whole family (if I didn’t eat like it was my last meal), for less than drive-thru Taco Bell costs. I don’t drink anymore but they had a pizza big enough for two to share and a bottle of wine for $20 as a special on Wednesday evenings.
That's 1995 prices, friends.

I have eaten food from street vendors to private chef's tables all over the world (all but two continents), and I will remember this pizza.

I am not from Atlanta, so this memory will be bittersweet, but I am VERY grateful I stopped in. The garlic knots were very good too, but the pizza was resplendent.

Ignore the low reviews. Some people will complain if they find a $100 bill with a ripped corner.

IF YOU ARE IN TOWN DO NOT LEAVE WITHOUT TRYING THIS AT LEAST ONCE.

Then twice.

Then once more on the way out of town.

Great work Atwoods!
You made a beat-up old veteran (and one beautiful little girl) very happy today.

God bless!

I have zero complaints about this place! It's a solid spot to grab some really good pizza. The portion size was perfect, and I genuinely enjoyed the freshness of the ingredients. The pizza wasn’t exactly mind-blowing or life-changing, but if you're looking for a cozy place with quality food and a relaxed atmosphere, this is it.

What stood out to me was the use of fresh, flavorful toppings paired with a great selection of beer. It’s clear they care about what they’re serving. The service was also attentive and friendly, adding to the overall experience. While it might not be a destination for a "wow" factor, it’s definitely a reliable go-to for a casual meal. If I’m ever in the area again, I’d definitely stop by for another round!

We came in after the lunch rush. It was nice and quiet, the cibes were good and fun. My husband recommended this place, and it said it was the best near Georgia Tech. Boy, was he right!! I ordered the Not So Mellow, and my husband got the Sho Me Your Roni. Both were phenomenal!! I was blown away by my pizza. It had mushroom cream, fior di latte, roasted mushrooms, red onion, goat cheese, truffle fig balsamic, and rosemary. The balance of sweet, sour, sweet, salty, and umami had me literally dancing in my seat!!! My husband's was a carnivore delight! It was meaty and not greasy at all!!! It had  red sauce, pepperoni, italian sausage, mozzarella-provolone, fior di latte, oregano, and Romano. This is now my top pizza place!!

I’d give this place 5 big booms! Do not do yourself a disservice by skipping the garlic knots—they’re a must. I wish I could tell you the names of the pizzas, but I gobbled them way too fast to remember!

name: Tropical Smoothie Cafe
address: 930 Spring St NW #001, Atlanta, GA 30309, USA

reviews.text: I truly enjoyed my experience here! I spent about 3–4 hours at the restaurant, and Mack and his team made sure everything ran smoothly. They were quick, efficient, and attentive. The atmosphere was great — the playlist set a nice vibe, and the bathrooms were spotless. Overall, I’m very happy with the service and will definitely be coming back!

This breakfast chicken wrap was either really good, or I was starving like Marvin. I believe it’s good. I never been here but thanks to Tmobile Tuesday deal, I’ll be back. I know the açaí bowl is gonna be yummy. I’ll dig n later.

Good music playing for the lunch crowd too.

Oh yeah parking can be a challenge, but that typical for that area.

I swung by Tropical Smoothie Cafe in Midtown Atlanta recently—and here’s my quick take:

The smoothies are made-to-order with fresh, high-quality ingredients that hit the spot whether you want something fruity, creamy, or packed with protein  . Service has been friendly and efficient; the staff seems genuinely upbeat and ready to help fuel your day  .

It’s conveniently located at 930 Spring St NW, making it easy to grab a smoothie before grabbing MARTA or popping into nearby shops and businesses  .

Overall, it’s a reliable, feel-good stop for a nutritious snack or quick breakfast in Midtown—cheerful staff, great smoothies, and perfect for when you need a little tropical pick-me-up.

I don’t usually leave reviews, but I had such a good experience at this tropical smoothie. Kai was so nice, she had a great attitude, & my smoothie was ON POINT. My family and I stopped here while on vacation and it was my grandmother’s first time at tropical smoothie. Kai was extremely patient with her and helped her figure out which smoothie she wanted. I find that to be rare these days. I really appreciated that experience.

The Mango Fruit smoothie was very fresh, went down smoothly, customer service was on point. They were fast with the orders. And if my memory is on point I think her name was kaii she was very welcoming. I 100% recommend going there. They will make your smoothie with love

name: Taco Bell
address: 930 Spring St NW Suite 4, Atlanta, GA 30309, USA

reviews.text: They wait for all the online ordered to be competed by the kitchen before they even distribute to all the people waiting. It’s exhausting. There isn’t a system between DoorDash or mobile order.

I recently visited the Taco Bell located in Midtown Atlanta at 930 Spring Street—and here’s my take:

The convenience factor is a big win: it’s open late (even until 5 AM on weekdays) and right by MARTA’s Midtown Station, making late-night cravings easy to satisfy  . The menu hits all the Taco Bell sweet spots—tacos, burritos, quesadillas, nachos, plus newer favorites like Crunchwrap Supreme, Mexican Pizza, and vegetarian-friendly options  .

Food was generally decent and prices felt fair, especially with the Cravings Value Menu offering a good deal  . I was impressed by how customizable everything was. Whether it’s made-to-order burritos or vegetarian tweaks, there's a lot of flexibility  .

On the downside, there are some inconsistent experiences. A few guests noted missing sauce packets in delivery orders, and others described odd service moments—the kind that make the vibe feel a bit hit-or-miss  .

Overall? If you're on the hunt for quick, affordable Tex-Mex-style fast food in Midtown, this Taco Bell delivers with solid options and after-hours accessibility. Just come in expecting that service and delivery experiences can vary.

We had a great experience at the Taco Bell on Spring St in downtown Atlanta. The restaurant was clean, the staff was friendly, and my order was prepared quickly and accurately.

The food was fresh and flavorful—my Crunchwrap Supreme, Chalupa and Dorito Tacos were delicious and well-portioned. I also liked the self-service kiosks, which made ordering easy.
1-2 hour wait time every time i’ve been here. extremely understaffed and crowded. feels like  taco bell from hell. don’t waste your time here you’ll never get your food.

I want to take a moment to give a heartfelt shout-out to a remarkable young lady named Cassandra. From the moment I walked in, her exceptional customer service skills stood out. Kassandra greeted me with a warm smile and a friendly attitude that made me feel welcome right away. I thought she was the manager, given the way she effortlessly guided me through my entire order. She took the time to answer all my questions, offered thoughtful recommendations, and ensured I had everything I needed. Her professionalism and genuine care really made my experience memorable.

name: Pho King Midtown
address: 950 W Peachtree St NW #240, Atlanta, GA 30309, USA

reviews.text: We had pho combo. Very good broth! The portion for a medium size is good! One recommendation is to have a bigger bowl so I could put more veggies in the soup base when it is hot. Will come again! It has free parking lot next to Publix. You could enter the restaurant from the door at the parking garage.

Yummy food as a proud 100% viet girl. I’m so glad I stumbled on this reasonably priced place especially because it was located so conveniently. The parking is street parking but we came at 12:30 and found parking right out front. The service was kind and quick. The decor and inside is nice and sleek.

We got the Bo luc lac (shaking beef) that also comes with a little bowl of broth and medium pho tai ($14). We got fried rice in the shaking beef and it was so buttery and soft. The beef itself was soft and flavorful as well. The pho was usual. Very much satisfied my cravings and I felt light but full after.

The cafe su da is so creamy almost like sweet chocolate milk but not unbearable strong still good though.

I ordered fried egg roll , spring roll, large combination pho, two bai Mai sandwich and a Thai tea to go and only spent $60 not only was that affordable my food was served within 15 mins and most importantly the food was so flavorful and delicious. Definitely coming back every chance I get. Must try

Delicious!!! I had chicken pho,
Really good, light flavor 😋 with fresh herbs!! Definitely coming back here.

I recently grabbed a bowl at Pho King in Midtown, and here’s how it went:

The pho often delivers serious flavor and hearty portions. One diner shared that the pho was “nothing short of perfection—rich, flavorful broth paired with fresh herbs, tender meats, and just the right amount of spice,” with generous servings that leave room for leftovers  . Fleeting visits also note the food as “incredibly delicious,” highlighting the combo pho and shrimp egg rolls, with ample noodles and meat that are well‑cooked  .

There are also reviews that call out inconsistencies: one mentioned that the chicken pho “was kinda lacking,” describing the broth as overly salty and flat, with sticky noodles and odd-tasting chicken  . Another praised the vegan pho as "excellent," with deeply flavorful broth, though some found the tofu a bit bland and chewy  .

Pho King offers a wide range of items beyond pho—think lemongrass chicken, papaya salad, Bo Luc Lac (shaking beef), banh mi, spring rolls, and bubble teas—with options to customize and accommodate dietary preferences  .

Summing it up: If you're craving a comforting, generous bowl of pho or other Vietnamese classics in Midtown, Pho King often delivers—just be aware, quality can vary from visit to visit.

name: Which Wich Peachtree Place
address: 915 W Peachtree St NW, Atlanta, GA 30309, USA

reviews.text:
Which Wich at Midtown (915 W Peachtree St NW) offers a fun, fast casual sandwich experience perfect for a quick lunch break. The ordering system—marking choices on a bag with a Sharpie—is unique and engaging, and it does help dishes feel personalized and fresh.

I popped in after running errands and found the service quick, which is a win when you’re on the go. The sandwiches are solid and customizable, so you can make it as basic or loaded as you’d like.

If you’re walking through Midtown and need a reliable, customizable bite, this is a great option. Just be mindful that reviews are mixed—some folks mention occasional quality issues—but for a casual, fast lunch fix, it hits the mark.

Always been a fan of which wich!! So glad which wich is close to my place! Love the black bean patty vegetarian wich. The toppings and sauces are delicious. I love their vanilla and Hershey’s milk shakes!! Must try. Would recommend this wich place to everyone!!🌱

I recently visited Which Wich for the first time, and I have to say, it was an incredible experience from start to finish. The sandwich selection is extensive, offering a variety of options for every taste and dietary preference. I opted for the 'Turkeywich', and it was one of the best sandwiches I've ever had! The ingredients were fresh, and the bread was perfectly toasted.

The customization options are fantastic, allowing you to build your sandwich exactly how you like it. I loved the idea of filling out a paper bag with my choices - it made the ordering process smooth and fun.

The staff at Which Wich were friendly and attentive, ensuring that my order was accurate and that I had everything I needed. The shop itself was clean, well-organized, and had a comfortable atmosphere that made for an enjoyable dining experience.

Whether you're a sandwich aficionado or just looking for a quick, delicious meal, I highly recommend Which Wich. I’ll definitely be coming back!

We had a very terrible experience at this location of which wich. They were missing ingredients which we mentioned but the employee just said you just cannot see the ingredients. How can we not see bell peppers, Banana peppers, etc and veggies. The employee kept going back and forth saying you just may not be able to see things on the sandwich. Very rude encounter and very bad service. All of our sandwiches were wrong.
My friend ordered a kids meal and it says that it comes with a sandwich, chips, drink, and a special treat. They refused to give my friend a special treat and I will therefore never be coming back.

name: Einstein Bros. Bagels
address: 800 Peachtree St NE, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text: Katherine is the absolute best! I visit this location from time to time on my way to work. Each visit she welcomes you with a smile and is very patient when taking orders. This is the type of energy needed for early morning visitors. I was feeling rushed and anxious to get to work when I walked in but her calming demeanor, warm words of kindness and pleasant voice was welcoming and to my surprise I relaxed and realized it's Friday and what the hell, I'll get there when I get there and not to mention I forgot to order my favorite coffee; Hazelnut Vanilla and she was kind enough to add it to my order! Einstein Bros. should sell it in K-Cups for us to make at home because I'd definitely buy it. I ordered an "All Nighter and Texas Brisket breakfast sandwiches that were hot and fresh!  Katherine - Keep making folks smile and providing such great customer service. You are appreciated! Also, go on and get your Suburban and ride baby ride (with the windows down!) Now, Einstein Bros. go on and give that woman a raise! She's a great asset to your establishment!

⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
Walked into Einstein Bros Bagels Midtown at 8 AM thinking I’d just grab a quick breakfast — left wondering if I’d accidentally joined a cult of bagel perfection. The smell hits you first: fresh, warm, carb-scented happiness. I ordered an Everything Bagel with shmear, and I swear the first bite was like being hugged by a New York deli in the middle of Atlanta. The staff moves like a well-oiled coffee-and-bagel machine, even during the morning rush, and they somehow remember regulars’ orders like it’s a neighborhood sitcom. Bonus points for the coffee — strong enough to wake up a grad student in finals week. If you’re anywhere near Midtown, skip the sad desk breakfast and come here. Your future self will thank you.

The food is amazing! The only thingggggg… the cashier used the same gloves to grab a bagel, answer their cell phone, and hand a customer a cup. 😔 Maybe a “no gloves at the register” policy would help. I get it though—it’s easy to just grab a bagel without thinking. 😔

Einstein bagrl has great infrastructure & setup. Their food has great varieties & taste.
However, recent experience were not pleasant & seems that quality is deteriorating.
They need to step up their game to keep the customers happy as not all customers would share their feedback & might switch.
Overall, the place offers everything to be a winner but need tighter controls.

Catherine is absolutely amazing! The food was incredible—fresh, flavorful, and beautifully prepared. The atmosphere was spotless, well-kept, and had such a clean, pleasant smell that made the experience even better. Catherine’s attention to detail, friendly attitude, and genuine dedication make her stand out. Highly recommend her and this place to anyone looking for great food and a welcoming environment!

name: The Consulate Restaurant
address: 10 10th St NW Suite P200, Atlanta, GA 30309, USA

reviews.text:
This is a fine dining experience that a lot of people in Atlanta don’t know about. Every quarter the menu changes based off a new country. The country is decided on “spin night,” which is the first Friday of every quarter. They give out raffle tickets and raffle off bottles of wine and the chance to spin the globe!

I’ve been here for several different countries, including Morocco, China, South Korea, Egypt, and most recently the Galápagos Islands. The chef is incredibly talented. She isn’t just making dishes from that country. She is putting her own spin on them. I’ve never had a bad meal. The cocktails also go with the theme and are delicious. In addition to the country-inspired dishes, they also keep their most popular dishes from countries before on “the resident menu.” So if you had something that really blew your mind, there’s a chance that it’ll still be there the next time!

Just a reminder that 18% gratuity is included in the bill, but we always tip a little bit extra because the service is top tier.

Walking in, The Consulate presents itself as a quaint hole in the wall. Upon entry, it was like stepping into a whole different world. The decor and ambiance are stunning and cozy, and the dishes were all absolutely phenomenal. Will definitely be back to try the new menu every 90 days. Everything was presented in a gorgeous manner, and sinking into the complex flavors with every bite was truly an experience. The bar is stocked with exotic options and hometown favorites, and the bartender has a devilishly heavy hand. JB was fantastic and guided us through the Galapagos Islands proficiently, despite the menu only having been out for a week. We will be returning for years to come. Truly and sincerely, hats off to the chef. You are an inspiration and an culinary aficionado.

This was an amazing Delayed Birthday experience! Our palates enjoyed each Country’s delights! Jordan was our server! He was very familiar with the entire menu and answered all of our questions!! Thanks so much for an unforgettable evening!!!!

Absolutely amazing! Everytime I come here i am absolutely amazed. Greg and Cheney are super knowledgeable about the entire menu, and their imagination with cocktails are second to none. We had the spin yesterday too, I can't wait to see how yall do Jamaica on your next menu!

This place is amazing. I enjoyed every minute and every area of it. Beautiful view and the food is made with love. The food is delivered fresh and hot. I did not think it would be so flavorful, but the chef made beautiful meals. Time was definitely put into everything.
And the waiter!!! He is amazing. So attentive, so knowledgeable. I am glad that this anniversary is one to remember 💕
I cannot wait to comeback again.

name: Fado Irish Pub
address: 933 Peachtree St NE, Atlanta, GA 30309, USA

reviews.text: Great time here for sure. I enjoyed the boxty quesadillas and a soft pretzel while knocking back some Guinness. The atmosphere is worth the drive alone. Makes me feel like I'm back in Dublin.

Haven’t been here for food, but you can’t beat the bottomless mules on Friday evenings. Extremely reasonable prices, friendly service (all of the times I was here the waitresses never let any of our cups go empty) and really fun vibes. I always try to go here with a group for an early night out and always have fun.

Absolutely the worst dining experience I’ve had in years. The bartender Holly was flat-out rude — when we politely reminded her about our water, she snapped back with “I only have two hands.” Meanwhile, she was cheerful and attentive to everyone else. We were ignored, our food took 45 minutes to arrive, and the entire vibe was dismissive. Terrible service, terrible attitude. Never coming back.

Made reservation for 5:30 on a Wednesday and was immediately seated. Service from Andrea was excellent.  Even jumped in and addressed table wobble without our even asking.   Food was excellent.  We took a chance on fish and chips and were not disappointed.  Very good.  I even liked the coleslaw. Fries were seasoned and delicious and hot.  Made it to our table fast. Will be returning.
Great food and service. I had the Irish breakfast. It was as good if not better than what I had in Ireland.

name: Sivas Hookah Lounge
address: 794 Juniper St NE, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text: Starting with the parking... designated lot to park was full, so we ended up parking in the lot behind that. Having to download an app just to pay for parking was a drag. Claimed some stairs up to the restaurant and was greeted by a security guard who checked our I.D. We we're then put on a waiting list for 20 minutes. The first floor was dark and loud and filled to capacity. We were led up two flights to the second floor, which was also dark and quite noisy. We sat in a corner half booth with my chair facing the others dining in that night. The food was great and the drinks were strong. We decided not to get a hookah this time. The staff were helpful and efficient. If I'm being honest, the music was a bit too loud for a conversation to be had over dinner. The floors played different songs, so it was difficult to relax as much as I'd like. I wouldn't recommend bringing someone here on a first date unless you intend on not talking the entire time.

Horrible experience. Came here with a group of women for a kick back. They wouldn’t even give us water before we ordered. Waiter was extremely rude. If it wasn’t late we would’ve left. Drinks and food were okay, you get what you pay for. The hookah options were okay but we could only get two tips even though it was a group of 6. A mess.

In town for work and wanted some good Mediterranean food. Their food was excellent - from the lentil soup to the stuffed mushrooms to the chicken kabobs. Everything was seasoned and cooked very well. I would go with white rice next time though instead of their Turkish rice. Customer service was also nice and prices very reasonable. My only complaint is other customers can get far too loud which made it hard to concentrate on work or relax while reading. Other customers were literally screaming so loud and so often out of excitement for a sports game at their friends sitting no more than 6-12 inches opposite them.

Parking was convenient and the music was good. We waited about 10 minutes to even be serviced, after that the service was consistent. Food & hookah were decent. There’s a place upstairs by the bathroom that is perfect for taking pictures.
Delicious Mediterranean American cuisine. My favorite thing that I tried was Chicken Kebab. But the Ribeye Steak was so juicy and flavorful too! AND they have a Live DJ too!

name: Blue India
address: 933 Peachtree St NE, Atlanta, GA 30309, USA

reviews.text: I've been to Blue India a couple of times for solo dining. I sat at the bar, and service was excellent. The staff is welcoming. Nice selection of cocktails. I had the "When Life Gives You Lemons," kind of a lemon martini. So refreshing and light! I had a fun starter: Crispy Bhindi Chaat, which is very thin strips of fried okra with house seasoning. Yum! If you like fried okra, I definitely recommend this. I had garlic prawns for main course. Delicious! Really nice atmosphere as well. Nice background music that fits Indian spot, but not too loud or intrustive. Nice touch. Lovely decor and vibe. I'll definitely be back.

Went there based on reviews, plus it’s open till 11PM. This place has good starters, average vibes and their curries are okish. But their Biryani was a total mess, both chicken and mutton. The portions were good enough but quality wise, food was below par. I’d recommend trying Veg dishes, Veg Kolhapuri and Chicken 65 was good, they also serve complimentary rice.

They have a nice see through kitchen with big glasses all over to see parathas being cooked.

This place is overhyped and costly comparatively is what I felt. The service was good and the waiter also mentioned that car parking is available for free for 2 hours for the guests, but we received this info too late. Rest, the food that matters the most was average I believe.

Nice experience unfortunately the day when I visited with family, their HVAC unit was not working and it was extremely hot inside. We ordered chicken 65 butter naan Samosa chaat classic tandoori chicken saffron butter chicken. The total bill was $81 out of all these things chicken 65 was nice Samosa chat was decent classic tandoori Chicken was below par And saffron butter Chicken was excessively sweet so all in all just OK, will I go again probably not.

A colleague recommended this place, so went for dinner. We ordered the saffron chicken butter masala, lamb rogan josh, and butter naan. Both curries came with a side of rice. The flavor, aroma, and texture of the gravies were excellent—authentic and delicious. Overall, we really enjoyed the Indian cuisine this restaurant has to offer.

We had a disappointing experience at Blue India. My friends and I arrived at 9:15 PM, well before the 10:00 PM closing time. Instead of being welcomed, we were abruptly told to leave because they were closing soon. The staff spoke to us bluntly, which felt very unprofessional and uninviting.

It's frustrating to be treated this way, especially when we arrived with enough time to enjoy a meal. I was looking forward to trying the food, but the lack of hospitality completely ruined the experience. I won't be returning.

name: 683 Midtown Bar and Bistro
address: 683 Peachtree St NE, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text: The bartender was awesome and gave us some good recommendations of where to visit and what to do while visiting.
A nice bar to enjoy sitting along Peachtree St when the weather is nice. The food is elegantly simple. Part of the Indigo Hotel midtown ATL.

If you make the mistake of not making reservations before a show at the FOX theatre then this place just across the street is a clean, fast option that can serve appetizers quickly. The food was very good. We had the chicken Quesadilla with avocado and it was great!!!

The food was well presented, and the taste was average. The burger I had was the house special, and I was left woundering where the special was.. the service was extreemly slow unless your sitting at the bar. I waited for my check for about 20 minutes. After I asked for it. All in all I wont be enjoying my $20 here at this bar anymore
It's impossible to contact the hotel. They don't respond to emails. We have a serious double-billing problem. Please provide a WhatsApp number.

name: Panda Express
address: 350 Ferst Drive Nw Wenn Student Center 104, Atlanta, GA 30332, USA

reviews.text:
Good portions however sodas are not refillable. Standard American Asian fares.

2024 August

Ordered through Uber eats but food still good temp to eat, noodles were dry and teriyaki chicken burnt on one side , but edible and still hadn't decent taste and wasn't dry. It wasnt bad bug not great
I had my first Panda Express meal in the U.S. at here and the plate (two kinds of meat and rice or noodle) costs $10 now. The mushroom chicken is pretty good.
The workers give disproportionate offerings of the entrees. I watched someone get a plate before me with more than 1 scoop of protein. When addressed, the server refused to remedy the situation.
Taste like your typical Panda Express, tho my noodles were a bit dry. Keep in mind, this is in the student center on Georgia Tech’s campus.

name: Henry's Midtown Tavern
address: 132 10th St NE, Atlanta, GA 30309, USA

reviews.text:
We had a good dining experience! Our server, Milan was very friendly and chatty, we enjoy his service! (But wish he could be a but more attentive, as our drink was not refilled proactively due to he was busy serving customers in different sections of the restaurant).

We were there on a Friday evening ~7pm, weather was nice, outdoor seating was very popular and indoor was pretty empty!

Food was over good and reasonable priced. Will consider to revisit when we are in the area!

Henry’s is a great place to hang out, especially on their dog friendly deck. However, I find that their food is hit or miss.

We ate brunch their this weekend. It was my first time inside and I was very underwhelmed. We were first seated at a table directly in line with the front door. When we asked to be moved the hostess was a little put out. It was crowded and very loud. Our waiter was more interested in socializing with everyone than taking care of our order and request.

In addition, our friend and I had probably the Worst chicken & gravy biscuit ever. The gravy had very little seasoning, the biscuit was under cooked and gummy. The chicken was a very small (probably frozen) chewy chicken breast. Neither of us finished our meal, had to track down our server to get our check.

Very disappointing experience!

One of the best restaurant patios in Midtown, maybe even Atlanta.
Service is super positive and friendly. Food is tasty! Had eggs Benedict and Chicago dog. Both delicious!

Fully recommended for good weather

Henry’s had a nice atmosphere, cool vibe, and the staff was friendly, checked on the table the perfect amount of times, but the food itself was pretty mediocre. I ordered some wings and I believe a couple of them were undercooked since they didn’t pull apart well and were quite pink. The ones that weren’t suspicious were pretty good. My friend ordered the Eggs Benedict, but it had a couple of eggshells in it. We sat inside as opposed to outside, at a rickety table, and we were pestered by gnats while we ate. But, for partial indoor/outdoor places like that, that’s kind of to be expected. It’s pet-friendly; I think it’s a hot spot for dog owners, because there were lots of doggies on the deck and lots of photos of them inside. So it’s probably the perfect place to stop by for a bite with your pup. (I’m not from the area, and this was just one experience.)

Great place, beautiful outdoor patio seating, absolutely loved the scenery of the city, cute dogs. Really good margaritas, very good appetizers. Highly recommend the salmon. Service was a bit slow however the atmosphere makes up for it!😍

name: Bulla Gastrobar
address: 60 11th St NE, Atlanta, GA 30309, USA

reviews.text:
We had an incredible meal and much of the magic came from the outstanding service and culinary talent behind the scenes.
Our server Rachel was amazing. She was warm, attentive, and incredibly knowledgeable about the menu. Her recommendations were spot-on, and she made us feel genuinely welcomed throughout the entire meal.
Chef Tony stopped by knowing I was a vegetarian and gave phenomenal recommendations.  every dish was beautifully presented. You can tell he puts real heart into his craft.
Between Chef Tony’s exceptional cooking and Rachel’s top-tier hospitality, this was one of the best dining experiences we’ve had in a long time. We’ll definitely be back and we’ll be asking for Rachel!

Fonzell was an amazing server… sweet, kind, and incredibly knowledgeable about the menu. He explained everything so well and gave us great recommendations. The sangrias were a great (red for my partner, white for me), and the food overall was delicious; especially the flan and the salmon plate. Not the biggest fan of the pancakes, but only because I wasn’t expecting the blueberry compote on top (didn’t know it was a compote thought berries would be mixed in the batter).

Chad was excellent! He was so kind and checked on us often to make sure all was well. We appreciated his menu suggestions and the pleasant conversation. Bulla never disappoints in food, service or ambiance! We’ll be back again soon; thanks Chad and Miguel!

I love me some tapas and drove past this one day so I decided to give it a try. The food was delicious, no issues there. Me and my sister shared patatas bravas, albondigas, tuna tartare, and the sautéed garlic shrimp. Also enjoyed my lavender margarita although I wish it had a touch more of lavender. Our server Tristan was great too. Food also came out super quick!

The only issue I had with the place was ambiance. I felt like it gave chain restaurant energy which is a shame for such a cute spot. The lighting was just a bit bright and the music was giving Panera. In fact the ambiance in general was giving Panera. I don’t know how else to explain it. The temperature was also very warm — I was sweating by the time we left. No hate to Bulla. I just think it could do with slightly dimmer lighting, more vibey music, and turn the AC up. Maybe some candles to give it more of a mood.

OMG OMG OMG
This is what I ordered:
Watermelon Salad
Grilled Octopus with corn purèe
Ham Croquettes with fig jelly
Smoked Salmon Montaditos with cream cheese
Montaditos with tomato marmalade
The food was phenomenal and as always trust THIS HEALTHY EATING BIG GIRL, I know what to eat and where to eat. Check out the photos too.
This is the place to go to when you are in the convention area of Atlanta, GA. Whewwww, this place made me shout and enjoy being FREE even more. The ambiance, Nhya, Chef Tony, Christina and all the staff made a huge impact and allowed me to be myself and love on folk.

name: Agora Midtown
address: 92 Peachtree Pl NE, Atlanta, GA 30309, USA

reviews.text: Had a great experience here. The meat was so flavorful and not dry - definitely try the lamb chops. The portions are smaller but if you get appetizers it’s a good size. Sek was such a great server. Quick service, very kind, great recommendations. Definitely would come back

This place is amazing! Their food is delicious and the atmosphere is incredible. It’s like dining in a fancy restaurant in Istanbul, but with a modern twist. The flavors are authentic and the ambiance is perfect. They’ve perfectly balanced tradition and modernity.

I sat at the bar since I was alone. AJ was a great server and bartender. The food was great and perfectly cooked. Just enough char and seasoning. Most of their seating is upstairs. Ambiance is casual but nice.
They also have free parking across the street.

I absolutely loved this place! The restaurant looks amazing, and it even has an upstairs area—we went up for the first time and were really impressed. The food was top-notch, and the staff was incredibly warm and friendly.

I will definitely, definitely recommend this place! Everything follows proper hygiene standards, they offer vegetarian options, and I really appreciated how attentive they were about checking for any allergies. Truly a great spot—highly recommend!

I absolutely love this restaurant. The service is phenomenal from the hostess to the waiter. It is kid friendly! Our daughters enjoyed the asude kebab - the chicken was tender and seasoned to perfection! The rice had ingredients they are too picky to enjoy but they did eat the white rice. We also had the shrimp saganaki for appetizer. It was ok - it could have used a bit more seasoning. We got warm pita to share with the table. The best item we ordered was the salmon plate - OMG so amazing! The salad it came with was so delicious and fresh! We love this restaurant and will go back for sure!

name: The Original J.R. Crickets in Midtown Atlanta
address: 129 North Avenue NE, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text:
Let me take a deep breath here before I start.

My wife and I were recommended this place because of the wings. Now, my lemony pepper wet was fantastic. I'll be honest. I can't take that away from them, they did great. Problem was communication and service was terrible! Firstly, my wife's wings were not to her liking and the server didn't have anything to say about that. Another thing that bothered me was if you don't read the walls, 18% gratuity will be automatically added to all guests dining in. That was not made apparent, just a " service charge" was on the payment screen.
The worst thing was upon finishing our meal. I tried to pay for my food for 25 minutes before our server finally came to our table to have us pay....that was AFTER my wife had to track someone down. This place wasn't even that busy. Both my wife and I have worked in the service industry as well and I am very disappointed. I really wanted to like this place and I really wanted to come back. Sadly I won't. Please pay attention to your receipt if you come to this place, and question things that look suspicious. I'll miss the lemony pepper wet, they were good....oh well.

This was a highly recommended restaurant, and I’m honestly confused how. For 10 wings, a handful of fries, and a cup of water… $16+?? Once we sat ourselves and got our order taken we waited no less than 15-20 minutes for our food. We received it and nothing was even fresh. My fries were cold, and the server had to grab another serving. Their wings are huge & nothing remotely spectacular. The fries were horrible.. no seasoned salt, plain salt, or anything for that matter.. just fried starchy fries🤢.
I say they’re overpriced & underwhelming. They also expect you to tip even though you aren’t even truly waited on. No water refills no anything. I asked another server for water (a black girl with short curly hair) she had a weird attitude and asked if i could “meet her at the front with it or do I want her to bring it to our table” ??? Um, bring it to the table please? I won’t ever be back

This business is charging a service fee for debit cards which is criminal. If you’re paying with a debit card and see a service fee on your bill ask them to remove it. The server I had didn’t know how to remove it so he removed the gratuity. I will report this business to my cardholder company.

I ordered the shrimp and fish. The shrimp tasted like sewage. It was really old tasting like it’s been out all day— sewage. I eat shrimp often so I know how it should not taste. The fries were trash but the tater tots are better. The “fish” I had tasted like it was from the frozen section at a store. The wings were hard and dry.

The space and atmosphere were decent. I won’t return but I guess it’s a good spot if you like mid food.

December 2024

Service: 5/5
YOLANDA
She is a very great waitress.
When my food was not up to par, she listened to me and communicated to management about the issue so that it could be replaced. Put drink orders were correct.
Thank you, sis.

Prices: 5/5
Reasonable pricing. Please see receipt!

Ambiance: 4/5
It’s giving classic atlanta restaurant.
In definite need of an upgrade, but then it would lose that gritty look of old Atlanta.

Taste/Textures: 4/5
My first fried chicken wrap was overcooked and crumbled.

The replacement grilled wrap was delicious.

I didn’t care for the fries…. Slightly overcooked in my opinion.

Value: 5/5

TLDR:

Hmmm… nothing stands out about this place, but it’s not HORRIBLE. Would not return.

Classic ATL spot! The wings are consistently crispy, sauced just right, and full of flavor. The lemon pepper hot is a must. No-frills, just great food and a vibe that feels like home. Always hits the spot!

name: Willy's Mexicana Grill
address: 725 W Peachtree St NW, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text:
derrick is wonderful! his customer service is superb!
the food is fresh and delicious !

I like Willy's burrito bowl. The male server was kind enough to change his gloves upon request. I forgot to ask the female server and when I realized it she had finished adding extras. She touched the pen, lifted additional containers to the main serving area and slid her hand along the counter area in front oft the food. I prayed hard and enjoyed my food. Come on with the glove changes! Please and thank you!
I have been eating at this Willy's since  2007, Same great food and service. I highly recommend this Willy's at AT&T food court. Consistency must  be attributed to the management staff.

I have been coming here for a while.  The service is usually good but today I got in line and they took two large call in orders ahead of me.  I will give it another shot but won't go back if it happens again.
Great location!! The food is always fresh and delicious and the staff is friendly, fast and professional...I have lunch there every chance I get!

name: Michael's Cafe
address: 1100 Spring St NW # 100, Atlanta, GA 30309, USA

reviews.text: Really good and super clean, the family that owns it are always kind, my favorites are the vegetable omelette, California club sandwich, curry chicken with rice, and their cookies!
1st time here and it's perfect great customer service and really good food especially the Phillies :)

Came in here one day to get out of the rain during a storm. I bought some of their chicken tenders as thanks for putting up with me dripping water in their restaurant. I'm glad I did - the food was delicious! Really affordable too. Nothing exotic on the menu, but that's fine - soups and sandwiches are always good.

Definitely stop by if you're in Midtown.

I had a great experience at this restaurant. I was in the area and was looking for a place to eat and found this little jewel. The food is simple but great. It is made to order and the owners are so sweet. The chicken tenders are to die for as well as the Philly Cheese Steak. If you are ever in the area give it a try.

I work in the building with Michael's Cafe, so I eat here a lot and it's always good. Cooked to order, breakfast and lunch are very good. I recommend the hash browns with everything (I can't remember the proper name, but "buster" is in there) with a side of bacon, it never disappoints and it's enough for two to share. The family that owns the cafe are extremely nice also.

name: Chick-fil-A
address: 725 W Peachtree St NE, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text: This place is the worst cfa ever it nasty trash is lefted in the bend over The Weeknd allow pest and rodents. Food is left unwrapped over The Weeknd and is served the following Monday. Roaches roam freely and ignored. The that customers purchase is cooked in the same grease as pork chop YES PORK CHOPS. The salad left is never fresh or washed. Food left out over The Weeknd. Sinks left dirty every night  The food is always undercooked due to not following cfa guidelines these people don’t change they’re glove eat here at your own risk!!!!!!

Very small place and few workers. I waited 30 minutes to receive a salad, and I realize that this salad is very small compared to other places of this type. Besides, it’s very expensive and the salad looks badly made.

We have come here 1-2 times since it’s opened. This was our proportions for hash browns between two different meals upon opening. 🙃 one was overly filled and the other barely had any. Good thing we were sharing bc if this was someone else’s meal I’d be even more annoyed 👎🏼

This was a chill Chic fil A experience. I was in and out and they got my order correct. The ladies at the counter were friendly and helpful with big smiles. It isninside the old ATT building by the way.
Highly recommend this place! The staff was attentive, the food was fantastic, and the atmosphere was comfortable. I’ll be back for sure!

name: Panera Bread
address: 1080 Peachtree St NE Suite 14, Atlanta, GA 30309, USA

reviews.text: Cameron and team did a great job of delivering good service late in the day. They kindly showed me how to use the kiosk and brightened my day. The chicken noodle soup and Mediterranean Veggie Sandwich were comforting while I was visiting from out of town. I can’t wait to enjoy the Blueberry muffin tomorrow for my breakfast. Friendly team, good execution late in the day. Keep up the good work!

Panera Bread is always a reliable go-to spot for fresh, quick meals. 🥗🥪 The menu has a great variety—whether you’re in the mood for a hearty soup in a bread bowl, a fresh salad, or a warm sandwich, you’ll find something satisfying. The atmosphere is cozy and welcoming, with plenty of space to sit and get some work done or catch up with friends over coffee.

Service is usually quick and friendly, and I appreciate that the food consistently tastes fresh. The self-service kiosks make ordering super convenient, and the free Wi-Fi is a nice bonus if you’re staying for a while. Prices are fair for the quality, and the portions leave you feeling full without being heavy.

Overall, Panera Bread is a dependable choice for a healthy-ish meal with a comfortable café vibe.

Big foodie here. I have been ordering the Mediterranean Veggie sandwich for years. Just ordered it and either they changed the recipe or it wasnt made the same way. It did not taste the same at all. It is missing it sweetness and the bread was a bit stiff. The sandwich overall wasn't bad but did not taste like the Panera recipe that I've been having for years. I guess I'll have to go to another Panera to confirm.

The staff here is always very accommodating and efficient. Tia is a true gem and should be acknowledged for her willingness to satisfy customers. I use the catering services for work and sometimes my clients are last minute but I can always depend on the team at 1080 to not only get the job done but do it quick and precise. Thank you Tia. Thank You Staff. Job Well Done.

We ordered for work place lunch today through Panera website. First we waited for the order, then found the food got stolen from door dash delivery guy. Then when we contacted the store and asked to speak to the manager they said they would remake and redeliver the order and update their website but never did. Had to order work place lunch at a local restaurant nearby. Really disappointed in service of Panera for not remaking and delivering food.

name: Chick-fil-A
address: 350 Ferst Dr NW, Atlanta, GA 30332, USA

reviews.text: Went to GT campus and found this Chick-fil-A inside the campus . Very useful for students.  It gets crowded during peak lunch times and breakfast time .. good service .. they are quite fast in orders. Priced ok. ✅ coffee was average . Hash browns were too  good ! Overall a good experience..

Conveniently located at Georgia Tech University Student Center. Good service & efficient. Crowded during lunch hour.

The soda pop drinks are refillable, that is free refills, just have queue in line. No DIY.

2024-AUG-21

They didn't cut the chicken in my salad then the lady told me it was because they can't cut fillets and I asked her how I should've asked for it and she told me to ask for it cut, then she gave me a plastic butterknife and told me to cut it myself. Also, the dressing they gave me was leaking. The salad leaves themselves were not fresh and tasted bitter.

We placed a catering order by calling the number listed. Originally, I had just a pickup order, but the young lady who took my order suggested a catering order would provide more food for less money. She was very helpful and courteous. The order was ready on time and everything was perfect.

Located in the first floor of the student center at Georgia Tech, this chick-fil-a is standard for the franchise, with the exception that the service is not as remarkable as most chick-fil-as. As for the food, it tastes standard and delicious, though the servicing sizes are of impressive.

name: Subway
address: 85 5th St NE 1st Floor, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text: Got a salad bowl with rotisserie chicken everything was excellent, except the cucumbers which were excessively ripe with large seeds. Seating very limited only two tables inside. Adequate tables outside though
They are super stingy with ingredients. I would definitely avoid this location. When I have asked for ingredients, they don’t even put the required amount and refuse to put more.

Misunderstanding with coupons/mobile ordering on my end, but when it happened, the employee got frustrated with me and threw my sandwich to another counter while he dealt with other orders. I understand that it was frustrating to deal with and there may have been a language barrier, but it was shoddy service nonetheless. And the Italian Herbs and Cheese bread tasted stale.

I love subway . I went down this morning at about 8:23 because they open at 8am . I wanted to get a subway club before I went to the train and lady tried to ignore me at the door. The sign says 8. Then after knocking on the door she said ten more minutes… bummer 😔

Avoid at all costs. All of the vegetables looked to be a day or two old , The worst of which was the lettuce which was clearly decomposing 🤢.

Other than the vegetables.. The bread was stale and the meat tasted as if it had been left out of a refrigerator for hours.

I could only eat half of my 6-in sub before feeling the slight urge to throw up my food.

I will not return to this location ever again.

name: Sankranti Indian Kitchen
address: 85 5th St NE Suite A, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text: I tried the paneer tacos 🌮 here, loved the taste of the tacos though I would like it if they’d make it on naan and not lacha parathas ( just my suggestion ) on the base of the tacos. The paneer veggie bowl taste delicious too. Loved the crunchy peas on the top, very creative bowl menu. The mango lassi taste delicious 🤤 though couldn’t taste cardamom in it which was mentioned in the ingredients list. I’d recommend this place to everyone. 🌱

I literally gave this place a 5-star review several months ago and have stood by that since it opened but I must say, as kind as the staff still are, the food quality has gone down. The portion sizes are also significantly smaller given that the place serves predominantly college students. Before they were stingy with just the protein but now so little curry and even so little toppings ... I feel like I'm eating just rice now. Looks like I need to find another go-to spot to eat :((
I am coming new In Atlanta move from California.i am order a Bonless Biryani no Salt Chicken is Not Cooked Better And Rice is look like &Taste 0 Level 😡😡👎🏻👎🏻👎🏻👎🏻

The night shift people serve very little food compared to the people in the afternoon shift. While I like the place due to a good taste I wouldn't recommend getting dinner here. Better for lunch. At the same time I wasn't given any side sauce. Not good. I had ordered chicken biryani

September 2025 review. The $4.95(each) mini Tea (Chai) was pathetic for a "freshly made" from a pump-thermos. May be new management or cook. Hope the otherwise good restaurant can do better.  Parking is difficult, allow extra time. Restaurant has seating inside & outside.

name: FRY & FORK
address: 85 5th St NW D1, Atlanta, GA 30332, USA

reviews.text:
Title: A Delightful Lunch Experience at Fry & Fork!

I recently had the pleasure of dining at Fry & Fork for lunch, and I must say, it was an exceptional experience! Although I only tried their incredible wings and fried rice, I was blown away by the flavors and the quality of the food.

The wings were nothing short of fantastic—crispy on the outside and juicy on the inside, with just the right amount of seasoning. They were definitely one of the best I’ve ever had! The fried rice complemented the wings perfectly, bursting with flavor and freshness. It was clear that a lot of care goes into their food preparation.

Even though I only sampled a couple of items from the menu, I have no doubt that everything else at Fry & Fork is equally excellent. The atmosphere was warm and inviting, making it a wonderful place to enjoy a meal.

I can’t wait to return for lunch and explore more of their menu. If you’re looking for a great dining experience, I highly recommend Fry & Fork! You won’t be disappointed.

Amazing! This was my first time visiting this business and I must say I’m impressed. I ordered the fish sandwich with medium spiced seasoning and fries. The meal was a 10 out of 10. The breading was cooked to perfection. Nicely seasoned all for a reasonable price. Another thing I noticed was that the owner was there watching interactions and customer satisfaction. I didn’t know who he was until I left but I love to see owners taking an active role in their business and getting feedback from customers. He made sure to ask how my food was and to made sure I had everything I needed. Will be back.

Let me tell you, Fry & Fork hit the spot tonight! I grabbed their catfish sandwich combo, and wow, that catfish was on point. Crispy on the outside, juicy on the inside - just what you want. Plus, the bun wasn't all bready and heavy, which kept things nice and balanced.

The fries (wedge style, FYI) were also crispy and perfect for dipping. And let's not forget the staff - super friendly and helpful!

Honestly, I can't wait to go back and try something else. Fry & Fork totally blew my taste buds away!

Starving and waiting hours for my mom in the hospital. I ordered a chicken philly and fries for delivery. It came so hot. Loaded with chicken and cheese, loaded. I got full from the chicken outside of the bun in the container. Cheese so gooey. I didnt get the onions and peppers. I believe it is all white meat chicken. It was grilled and juicy. The bun could barely hold the chicken and cheese. Steak fries were good. I will definitely try this place again next time I'm in Atlanta.

This place has some of the best chicken sandwiches, chicken fingers, and chicken teriyaki I've ever had. But their fried fish is the absolute bomb! The fried fish and fried rice combo is my go-to. The staff is super friendly, the food is always on point, and the place is always spotless. I highly recommend checking it out!

The food is nice and hits the spot. The staff was friendly and patient with my giftcard. The only major complaint I have is with the app itself. Online ordering almost never works and I keep getting error messages. Other than that, the actual location and food are fine.

name: Asian Fusion
address: 75 5th St NW #170, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA

reviews.text: I bought fried rice but it’s cooked in a rice cooker so it’s wet and mushy. The Mongolian beef is pretty good, the service could be better. 4/7 (would recommend if you’re hungry with limited options). The spring roll was pretty good.

Asian Fusion in Tech Square offers a pleasant and modern dining experience featuring a creative mix of Asian flavors all in one spot. The restaurant’s elegant, contemporary décor creates a cozy ambiance that makes it great for both a quick meal or a laid-back dinner outing. Many diners rave about the "awesome" food, calling the spot a "must‑eat in town" with “fabulous food & flawless service” and “speechless” performance overall.  The menu blends sushi, hibachi, and classic Chinese dishes, and many reviewers on delivery platforms praise the sushi—especially rolls like the Atlanta Roll and spicy tuna—as consistently fresh and flavorful.  It’s a go-to for those craving variety, quality, and a relaxed Tech Square dining vibe.

NOT the spot for sushi. Got the Dragon roll and it was kind of a rough mushy mess. Take a look, do you want to eat that? And where's the eel?? And it was $13. Called the manager, he said there is nothing wrong with it. lol. ok! What a shame.

Post owner response: Trust me, this sushi was like wet garbage. I have no problem with 'value' sushi. THIS was not that. I took the time to txt you photos and you want me to come back to your place for $13?! You're just dumb.

I had an incredible dining experience at this Asian Fusion restaurant! From the moment I walked in, the ambiance was inviting and cozy, setting the perfect mood for a delicious meal.
